{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LGdRmY1ciiUsiZihXZ1qp4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile the final report:\n\n## Cloche Architecture: Complete Exploration Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here's the complete architectural picture:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **CLI Command Structure** (`cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\nThe CLI client is a short-lived gRPC client with these commands:\n\n**Non-daemon commands** (no gRPC connection needed):\n- `init` — Initialize a Cloche project\n- `health` — Show project health summary\n- `get <key>` — Get a value from run context store\n- `set <key> <value>` — Set a value in run context store\n- `tasks` — Show task pipeline and assignment state (uses HTTP API)\n\n**Daemon commands** (gRPC):\n- `run --workflow <name>` — Launch a container or host workflow run\n- `status <run-id>` — Check run status\n- `logs <run-id>` — Stream run logs\n- `poll <run-id>` — Wait for run to complete\n- `list [--all]` — List runs\n- `stop <run-id>` — Stop a running workflow\n- `delete <container-or-run-id>` — Delete a retained container\n- `loop [--max <n>]` — Start orchestration loop\n- `shutdown` — Shut down daemon\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Workflow DSL Files** (`.cloche/*.cloche`)\n\n**Location-based execution:**\n- **Container workflows** (e.g., `.cloche/develop.cloche`) — Run inside Docker via `cloche-agent`. Steps: `agent` or `script` only.\n- **Host workflows** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — Run on host machine by daemon. Steps: `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type.\n\n**Multi-workflow support:**\n- Host workflows can define multiple named workflows: `list-tasks`, `main`, `finalize` (only `main` required)\n- Daemon orchestrates in 3 phases:\n  1. `list-tasks` → discovers work (outputs JSONL)\n  2. `main` → processes task (receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var)\n  3. `finalize` → cleanup (receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID`)\n\n**Example workflow structure:**\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step test {\n    run = \"go test ./...\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> implement\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Domain Types** (`internal/domain/`)\n\n**Key types in `workflow.go`:**\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n  Name      string\n  Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n  Steps     map[string]*Step\n  Wiring    []Wire\n  Collects  []Collect\n  EntryStep string\n  Config    map[string]string // workflow-level config (e.g., \"container.image\")\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n  Name    string\n  Type    StepType  // \"agent\", \"script\", or \"workflow\"\n  Results []string\n  Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n  From      string\n  Result    string\n  To        string\n  OutputMap []OutputMapping\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n  EnvVar string\n  Path   OutputPath\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n  Segments []PathSegment  // chain of field accesses and array indices\n}\n```\n\n**Key types in `run.go`:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID             string\n  WorkflowName   string\n  State          RunState  // \"pending\", \"running\", \"succeeded\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\n  ActiveSteps    []string\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n  IsHost         bool  // true for host workflow runs\n  ParentRunID    string  // links child runs to parent\n  Title          string\n  BaseSHA        string  // for git branch creation\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n  StepName    string\n  Result      string\n  StartedAt   time.Time\n  CompletedAt time.Time\n  Logs        string\n  GitRef      string  // output state (git branch)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Ports (Interfaces)** (`internal/ports/`)\n\n**RunStore** — Persistence for runs and their state:\n```go\ninterface RunStore {\n  CreateRun(ctx, run) error\n  GetRun(ctx, id) (*Run, error)\n  UpdateRun(ctx, run) error\n  ListRuns(ctx, since) ([]*Run, error)\n  ListChildRuns(ctx, parentRunID) ([]*Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n**CaptureStore** — Persists step execution logs and metadata\n\n**LogStore** — Stores log files by run and step\n\n**EvolutionStore** — Tracks workflow self-evolution changes\n\n**Agent adapters** implement:\n```go\ninterface StepExecutor {\n  Execute(ctx, step) (result string, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Data Passing Between Steps**\n\n**Three mechanisms:**\n\n1. **Output Mappings (Wire expressions)** — Extract values from previous step output and inject as env vars:\n   ```\n   ready-tasks:success -> claim-task [\n     CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output[0].id,\n     CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title\n   ]\n   ```\n   Supported path expressions:\n   - `output` — raw output string\n   - `output.field` — JSON object field\n   - `output[N]` — JSON array index\n   - `output.a.b.c[0].d` — chained access\n\n2. **Step Output Files** — Each step writes to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n   - Host executor reads previous step output via `findPrevOutput()` \n   - Resolves `prompt_step` config or wiring graph to find source\n\n3. **Run Context Store** (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`) — Shared key-value store:\n   - CLI: `cloche get <key>` / `cloche set <key> <value>`\n   - Accesses: `runcontext.Get(projectDir, runID, key)` / `runcontext.Set(...)`\n   - Thread-safe JSON file (not at-rest distributed)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Host Workflow Executor** (`internal/host/`)\n\n**Executor type** implements `engine.StepExecutor`:\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n  ProjectDir    string        // actual project directory\n  MainDir       string        // main branch worktree (for scripts)\n  Dispatcher    RunDispatcher // gRPC client to dispatch container runs\n  Store         ports.RunStore\n  OutputDir     string        // .cloche/<run-id>/output\n  Wires         []domain.Wire // for output mappings\n  HostRunID     string        // parent run ID\n  TaskID        string        // assigned by daemon loop\n  ExtraEnv      []string      // additional env vars\n}\n```\n\n**Three step types:**\n\n1. **Script** (`executeScript`) — Runs shell commands via `sh -c`\n   - Executes from `MainDir` (main worktree, not linked worktree)\n   - Env vars: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`\n   - Resolves output mappings, injects them as env vars\n   - Extracts result via `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker\n\n2. **Workflow** (`executeWorkflow`) — Dispatches container run and waits\n   - Calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()` to launch container run via gRPC\n   - Links child run to parent: `childRun.ParentRunID = hostRunID`\n   - Polls run state until terminal (success/fail/cancelled)\n   - Writes run ID to step output file for downstream steps\n\n3. **Agent** (`executeAgent`) — Runs agent command on host\n   - Uses `prompt.Adapter` (Claude Code or other agents)\n   - Copies previous step output to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Reads output from adapter's location to executor's output path\n\n**Runner type** orchestrates host workflow execution:\n- `RunNamed(ctx, projectDir, workflowName)` — executes named workflow from `host.cloche`\n- Creates `Executor`, wraps with `engine.Engine`\n- Persists host run in store, handles step events\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Container Agent Executor** (`cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`, `internal/agent/`)\n\nRuns inside container, autonomous execution without human intervention.\n\n**Runner** receives:\n- `workflowPath` — path to `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche` inside container\n- `workDir` — `/workspace` inside container\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` env var — for per-run data in `/workspace/.cloche/<run-id>`\n\n**stepExecutor** dispatches to adapters:\n```go\ntype stepExecutor struct {\n  workDir      string\n  generic      *generic.Adapter   // script execution\n  prompt       *prompt.Adapter    // agent (Claude Code)\n  logStream    *logstream.Writer  // unified log\n  statusWriter *protocol.StatusWriter\n}\n```\n\n**Status messages** (JSON, one per line to stdout):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",...}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"result\":\"success\",...}\n{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",...}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Existing \"Get\" and \"Set\" Commands**\n\nLocated in `cmd/cloche/main.go`:\n\n```go\nfunc cmdGet(args []string) {\n  projectDir, runID := resolveRunContext()  // CLOCHE_RUN_ID env var\n  val, ok, err := runcontext.Get(projectDir, runID, args[0])\n  // Accesses .cloche/<run-id>/context.json\n}\n\nfunc cmdSet(args []string) {\n  projectDir, runID := resolveRunContext()\n  err := runcontext.Set(projectDir, runID, args[0], args[1])\n  // Updates .cloche/<run-id>/context.json (JSON map)\n}\n```\n\n**Usage in workflows:**\n- Called from shell steps: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<id> cloche get <key>`\n- Requires `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` and `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` env vars set\n- Thread-safe within a process, but no distributed locking\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Inter-Step Data Passing: Summary**\n\n| Mechanism | Storage | Usage | Scope |\n|-----------|---------|-------|-------|\n| **Output Mappings** | `.cloche/<run-id>/output/*.out` | Env vars injected into next step via wire expressions | Within single run |\n| **Output Files** | `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step>.out` | Read by subsequent steps via wiring/`prompt_step` | Within single run |\n| **Run Context** | `.cloche/<run-id>/context.json` | Shared key-value store (JSON), CLI: `cloche get/set` | Within single run |\n| **Shell Env** | Process environment | Passed by executor to step command | Within step execution |\n| **Git Branches** | Git refs | Results extracted to branches, `GitRef` in StepExecution | Across runs |\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Engine Architecture** (`internal/engine/`)\n\nCore workflow execution engine (generic, not aware of host vs container):\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n  executor       StepExecutor  // inject your executor\n  status         StatusHandler // notifications\n  maxSteps       int\n  defaultTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx, wf *Workflow) (*Run, error) {\n  // 1. Launch entry step\n  // 2. Main event loop: wait for results, follow wiring\n  // 3. Support fanout (multiple wire targets)\n  // 4. Support collect() for join conditions\n  // 5. Return final run state\n}\n```\n\n**Execution model:**\n- Launches entry step in goroutine\n- Receives result on channel\n- Looks up next steps via `wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)`\n- Supports fanout (parallel branches)\n- Supports `collect all(...)` / `collect any(...)` for synchronization\n\n---\n\n### 11. **File Paths and Directories**\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche          # Container workflow\n│   ├── host.cloche             # Host workflow (3 phases)\n│   ├── <run-id>/\n│   │   ├── context.json        # Run context store (key-value)\n│   │   ├── prompt.txt          # Per-run prompt (read by agent)\n│   │   └── output/\n│   │       ├── <step>.out      # Step output files\n│   │       ├── <step>.log      # Agent/script log\n│   │       └── llm-<step>.log  # LLM-specific log\n│   ├── prompts/                # Prompt templates\n│   ├── scripts/                # Host-side scripts\n│   └── overrides/              # Files applied on top of /workspace in container\n├── cmd/cloche/main.go          # CLI client\n├── cmd/cloched/main.go         # Daemon\n├── cmd/cloche-agent/main.go    # Container entrypoint\n└── ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Key Result Marker Mechanism**\n\nSteps declare their possible results:\n```cloche\nstep test {\n  run = \"go test\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\nSteps report results via:\n1. **Explicit marker:** Last line contains `CLOCHE_RESULT:success` or `CLOCHE_RESULT:fail`\n2. **Exit code:** Success (exit 0) → \"success\", Failure (exit 1) → \"fail\"\n\nThe `protocol.ExtractResult()` function scans output and removes marker lines.\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Summary of Key Components**\n\n| Component | Path | Role |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| **DSL Parser** | `internal/dsl/parser.go` | Parses `.cloche` files into `Workflow` structs |\n| **Engine** | `internal/engine/engine.go` | Executes workflow graph, manages step lifecycle |\n| **Host Executor** | `internal/host/executor.go` | Implements `StepExecutor` for host steps |\n| **Host Runner** | `internal/host/runner.go` | Orchestrates host workflow phases |\n| **Agent Runner** | `internal/agent/runner.go` | Orchestrates container workflow inside container |\n| **Prompt Adapter** | `internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` | Invokes Claude Code or other agent commands |\n| **Generic Adapter** | `internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` | Runs shell scripts |\n| **Run Context Store** | `internal/runcontext/store.go` | Per-run key-value JSON store |\n| **SQLite Store** | `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Implements `RunStore`, `LogStore`, `EvolutionStore` |\n| **Docker Runtime** | `internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` | Implements `ContainerRuntime` |\n| **gRPC Server** | `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Daemon's gRPC interface for CLI |\n| **Status Writer** | `internal/protocol/status.go` | JSON-encoded status messages (stdout) |\n\n---\n\n### 14. **Complete Picture: Data Flow**\n\n**Container workflow execution:**\n1. User: `cloche run --workflow develop`\n2. CLI sends `RunWorkflowRequest` via gRPC\n3. Daemon launches container with `cloche-agent <workflow-file>`\n4. Agent inside container:\n   - Parses workflow DSL\n   - Launches entry step (via `prompt` or `generic` adapter)\n   - Step writes `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker or relies on exit code\n   - Agent reads result, follows wiring, launches next step(s)\n   - Logs to unified log and status writer (JSON to stdout)\n   - Persists step outputs to `.cloche/output/*.log`\n\n**Host workflow execution:**\n1. Daemon detects host.cloche exists\n2. Runs `host.runner.RunNamed(ctx, \"list-tasks\")`\n   - Executes list-tasks workflow (script steps only)\n   - Parses output as JSONL, picks first open task\n3. Runs `host.runner.RunNamed(ctx, \"main\", taskID)`\n   - Executes script/workflow/agent steps\n   - `workflow` steps dispatch container runs via gRPC\n   - Waits for container runs to complete\n   - Can pass data via output mappings\n4. Runs `host.runner.RunNamed(ctx, \"finalize\")`\n   - Cleanup step regardless of main outcome\n\n**Data passing:**\n- Output mappings: Extract JSON from previous step → env vars\n- Output files: Read from `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n- Run context: Shared JSON key-value store\n- Env vars: Injected by executor into next step\n\n---\n\nThis architecture provides a flexible, extensible system for autonomous workflow execution with clear separation of concerns (DSL parsing, execution engine, adapters) and composable data-passing mechanisms suitable for AI-driven development tasks."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a239bc3510c30de23 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74062\ntool_uses: 30\nduration_ms: 66156</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5096be8a-dfc2-4986-a448-2dc8a604d8e8","uuid":"690cfc68-bf1b-47b6-bffe-ed446242f3e5","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase thoroughly to understand:\n\n1. The CLI command structure in cmd/cloche/ - how subcommands are registered\n2. The workflow DSL files (.cloche files) - find all of them and read their contents\n3. The domain types for workflows, steps, and results\n4. The ports/interfaces especially RunStore, any existing key-value or data passing mechanisms\n5. The host workflow executor in internal/host/\n6. The agent workflow executor (cloche-agent)\n7. Any existing \"get\" or \"set\" command implementations\n8. How inter-step data passing currently works (JSON output mappings, wiring)\n\nRead all relevant files fully. I need a complete picture of the architecture.","agentId":"a239bc3510c30de23","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile the final report:\n\n## Cloche Architecture: Complete Exploration Report\n\nI've conducted a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here's the complete architectural picture:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **CLI Command Structure** (`cmd/cloche/main.go`)\n\nThe CLI client is a short-lived gRPC client with these commands:\n\n**Non-daemon commands** (no gRPC connection needed):\n- `init` — Initialize a Cloche project\n- `health` — Show project health summary\n- `get <key>` — Get a value from run context store\n- `set <key> <value>` — Set a value in run context store\n- `tasks` — Show task pipeline and assignment state (uses HTTP API)\n\n**Daemon commands** (gRPC):\n- `run --workflow <name>` — Launch a container or host workflow run\n- `status <run-id>` — Check run status\n- `logs <run-id>` — Stream run logs\n- `poll <run-id>` — Wait for run to complete\n- `list [--all]` — List runs\n- `stop <run-id>` — Stop a running workflow\n- `delete <container-or-run-id>` — Delete a retained container\n- `loop [--max <n>]` — Start orchestration loop\n- `shutdown` — Shut down daemon\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Workflow DSL Files** (`.cloche/*.cloche`)\n\n**Location-based execution:**\n- **Container workflows** (e.g., `.cloche/develop.cloche`) — Run inside Docker via `cloche-agent`. Steps: `agent` or `script` only.\n- **Host workflows** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) — Run on host machine by daemon. Steps: `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type.\n\n**Multi-workflow support:**\n- Host workflows can define multiple named workflows: `list-tasks`, `main`, `finalize` (only `main` required)\n- Daemon orchestrates in 3 phases:\n  1. `list-tasks` → discovers work (outputs JSONL)\n  2. `main` → processes task (receives `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var)\n  3. `finalize` → cleanup (receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID`)\n\n**Example workflow structure:**\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  step test {\n    run = \"go test ./...\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n  \n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> implement\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Domain Types** (`internal/domain/`)\n\n**Key types in `workflow.go`:**\n```go\ntype Workflow struct {\n  Name      string\n  Location  WorkflowLocation  // \"container\" or \"host\"\n  Steps     map[string]*Step\n  Wiring    []Wire\n  Collects  []Collect\n  EntryStep string\n  Config    map[string]string // workflow-level config (e.g., \"container.image\")\n}\n\ntype Step struct {\n  Name    string\n  Type    StepType  // \"agent\", \"script\", or \"workflow\"\n  Results []string\n  Config  map[string]string\n}\n\ntype Wire struct {\n  From      string\n  Result    string\n  To        string\n  OutputMap []OutputMapping\n}\n\ntype OutputMapping struct {\n  EnvVar string\n  Path   OutputPath\n}\n\ntype OutputPath struct {\n  Segments []PathSegment  // chain of field accesses and array indices\n}\n```\n\n**Key types in `run.go`:**\n```go\ntype Run struct {\n  ID             string\n  WorkflowName   string\n  State          RunState  // \"pending\", \"running\", \"succeeded\", \"failed\", \"cancelled\"\n  ActiveSteps    []string\n  StepExecutions []*StepExecution\n  IsHost         bool  // true for host workflow runs\n  ParentRunID    string  // links child runs to parent\n  Title          string\n  BaseSHA        string  // for git branch creation\n}\n\ntype StepExecution struct {\n  StepName    string\n  Result      string\n  StartedAt   time.Time\n  CompletedAt time.Time\n  Logs        string\n  GitRef      string  // output state (git branch)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Ports (Interfaces)** (`internal/ports/`)\n\n**RunStore** — Persistence for runs and their state:\n```go\ninterface RunStore {\n  CreateRun(ctx, run) error\n  GetRun(ctx, id) (*Run, error)\n  UpdateRun(ctx, run) error\n  ListRuns(ctx, since) ([]*Run, error)\n  ListChildRuns(ctx, parentRunID) ([]*Run, error)\n}\n```\n\n**CaptureStore** — Persists step execution logs and metadata\n\n**LogStore** — Stores log files by run and step\n\n**EvolutionStore** — Tracks workflow self-evolution changes\n\n**Agent adapters** implement:\n```go\ninterface StepExecutor {\n  Execute(ctx, step) (result string, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Data Passing Between Steps**\n\n**Three mechanisms:**\n\n1. **Output Mappings (Wire expressions)** — Extract values from previous step output and inject as env vars:\n   ```\n   ready-tasks:success -> claim-task [\n     CLOCHE_TASK_ID = output[0].id,\n     CLOCHE_TASK_TITLE = output[0].title\n   ]\n   ```\n   Supported path expressions:\n   - `output` — raw output string\n   - `output.field` — JSON object field\n   - `output[N]` — JSON array index\n   - `output.a.b.c[0].d` — chained access\n\n2. **Step Output Files** — Each step writes to `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step-name>.out`\n   - Host executor reads previous step output via `findPrevOutput()` \n   - Resolves `prompt_step` config or wiring graph to find source\n\n3. **Run Context Store** (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`) — Shared key-value store:\n   - CLI: `cloche get <key>` / `cloche set <key> <value>`\n   - Accesses: `runcontext.Get(projectDir, runID, key)` / `runcontext.Set(...)`\n   - Thread-safe JSON file (not at-rest distributed)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Host Workflow Executor** (`internal/host/`)\n\n**Executor type** implements `engine.StepExecutor`:\n```go\ntype Executor struct {\n  ProjectDir    string        // actual project directory\n  MainDir       string        // main branch worktree (for scripts)\n  Dispatcher    RunDispatcher // gRPC client to dispatch container runs\n  Store         ports.RunStore\n  OutputDir     string        // .cloche/<run-id>/output\n  Wires         []domain.Wire // for output mappings\n  HostRunID     string        // parent run ID\n  TaskID        string        // assigned by daemon loop\n  ExtraEnv      []string      // additional env vars\n}\n```\n\n**Three step types:**\n\n1. **Script** (`executeScript`) — Runs shell commands via `sh -c`\n   - Executes from `MainDir` (main worktree, not linked worktree)\n   - Env vars: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_RUN_ID`, `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`\n   - Resolves output mappings, injects them as env vars\n   - Extracts result via `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker\n\n2. **Workflow** (`executeWorkflow`) — Dispatches container run and waits\n   - Calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()` to launch container run via gRPC\n   - Links child run to parent: `childRun.ParentRunID = hostRunID`\n   - Polls run state until terminal (success/fail/cancelled)\n   - Writes run ID to step output file for downstream steps\n\n3. **Agent** (`executeAgent`) — Runs agent command on host\n   - Uses `prompt.Adapter` (Claude Code or other agents)\n   - Copies previous step output to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`\n   - Reads output from adapter's location to executor's output path\n\n**Runner type** orchestrates host workflow execution:\n- `RunNamed(ctx, projectDir, workflowName)` — executes named workflow from `host.cloche`\n- Creates `Executor`, wraps with `engine.Engine`\n- Persists host run in store, handles step events\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Container Agent Executor** (`cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`, `internal/agent/`)\n\nRuns inside container, autonomous execution without human intervention.\n\n**Runner** receives:\n- `workflowPath` — path to `.cloche/<workflow>.cloche` inside container\n- `workDir` — `/workspace` inside container\n- `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` env var — for per-run data in `/workspace/.cloche/<run-id>`\n\n**stepExecutor** dispatches to adapters:\n```go\ntype stepExecutor struct {\n  workDir      string\n  generic      *generic.Adapter   // script execution\n  prompt       *prompt.Adapter    // agent (Claude Code)\n  logStream    *logstream.Writer  // unified log\n  statusWriter *protocol.StatusWriter\n}\n```\n\n**Status messages** (JSON, one per line to stdout):\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",...}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"implement\",\"result\":\"success\",...}\n{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",...}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Existing \"Get\" and \"Set\" Commands**\n\nLocated in `cmd/cloche/main.go`:\n\n```go\nfunc cmdGet(args []string) {\n  projectDir, runID := resolveRunContext()  // CLOCHE_RUN_ID env var\n  val, ok, err := runcontext.Get(projectDir, runID, args[0])\n  // Accesses .cloche/<run-id>/context.json\n}\n\nfunc cmdSet(args []string) {\n  projectDir, runID := resolveRunContext()\n  err := runcontext.Set(projectDir, runID, args[0], args[1])\n  // Updates .cloche/<run-id>/context.json (JSON map)\n}\n```\n\n**Usage in workflows:**\n- Called from shell steps: `CLOCHE_RUN_ID=<id> cloche get <key>`\n- Requires `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` and `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` env vars set\n- Thread-safe within a process, but no distributed locking\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Inter-Step Data Passing: Summary**\n\n| Mechanism | Storage | Usage | Scope |\n|-----------|---------|-------|-------|\n| **Output Mappings** | `.cloche/<run-id>/output/*.out` | Env vars injected into next step via wire expressions | Within single run |\n| **Output Files** | `.cloche/<run-id>/output/<step>.out` | Read by subsequent steps via wiring/`prompt_step` | Within single run |\n| **Run Context** | `.cloche/<run-id>/context.json` | Shared key-value store (JSON), CLI: `cloche get/set` | Within single run |\n| **Shell Env** | Process environment | Passed by executor to step command | Within step execution |\n| **Git Branches** | Git refs | Results extracted to branches, `GitRef` in StepExecution | Across runs |\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Engine Architecture** (`internal/engine/`)\n\nCore workflow execution engine (generic, not aware of host vs container):\n\n```go\ntype Engine struct {\n  executor       StepExecutor  // inject your executor\n  status         StatusHandler // notifications\n  maxSteps       int\n  defaultTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\nfunc (e *Engine) Run(ctx, wf *Workflow) (*Run, error) {\n  // 1. Launch entry step\n  // 2. Main event loop: wait for results, follow wiring\n  // 3. Support fanout (multiple wire targets)\n  // 4. Support collect() for join conditions\n  // 5. Return final run state\n}\n```\n\n**Execution model:**\n- Launches entry step in goroutine\n- Receives result on channel\n- Looks up next steps via `wf.NextSteps(stepName, result)`\n- Supports fanout (parallel branches)\n- Supports `collect all(...)` / `collect any(...)` for synchronization\n\n---\n\n### 11. **File Paths and Directories**\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── .cloche/\n│   ├── develop.cloche          # Container workflow\n│   ├── host.cloche             # Host workflow (3 phases)\n│   ├── <run-id>/\n│   │   ├── context.json        # Run context store (key-value)\n│   │   ├── prompt.txt          # Per-run prompt (read by agent)\n│   │   └── output/\n│   │       ├── <step>.out      # Step output files\n│   │       ├── <step>.log      # Agent/script log\n│   │       └── llm-<step>.log  # LLM-specific log\n│   ├── prompts/                # Prompt templates\n│   ├── scripts/                # Host-side scripts\n│   └── overrides/              # Files applied on top of /workspace in container\n├── cmd/cloche/main.go          # CLI client\n├── cmd/cloched/main.go         # Daemon\n├── cmd/cloche-agent/main.go    # Container entrypoint\n└── ...\n```\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Key Result Marker Mechanism**\n\nSteps declare their possible results:\n```cloche\nstep test {\n  run = \"go test\"\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\nSteps report results via:\n1. **Explicit marker:** Last line contains `CLOCHE_RESULT:success` or `CLOCHE_RESULT:fail`\n2. **Exit code:** Success (exit 0) → \"success\", Failure (exit 1) → \"fail\"\n\nThe `protocol.ExtractResult()` function scans output and removes marker lines.\n\n---\n\n### 13. **Summary of Key Components**\n\n| Component | Path | Role |\n|-----------|------|------|\n| **DSL Parser** | `internal/dsl/parser.go` | Parses `.cloche` files into `Workflow` structs |\n| **Engine** | `internal/engine/engine.go` | Executes workflow graph, manages step lifecycle |\n| **Host Executor** | `internal/host/executor.go` | Implements `StepExecutor` for host steps |\n| **Host Runner** | `internal/host/runner.go` | Orchestrates host workflow phases |\n| **Agent Runner** | `internal/agent/runner.go` | Orchestrates container workflow inside container |\n| **Prompt Adapter** | `internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` | Invokes Claude Code or other agent commands |\n| **Generic Adapter** | `internal/adapters/agents/generic/generic.go` | Runs shell scripts |\n| **Run Context Store** | `internal/runcontext/store.go` | Per-run key-value JSON store |\n| **SQLite Store** | `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Implements `RunStore`, `LogStore`, `EvolutionStore` |\n| **Docker Runtime** | `internal/adapters/docker/runtime.go` | Implements `ContainerRuntime` |\n| **gRPC Server** | `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Daemon's gRPC interface for CLI |\n| **Status Writer** | `internal/protocol/status.go` | JSON-encoded status messages (stdout) |\n\n---\n\n### 14. **Complete Picture: Data Flow**\n\n**Container workflow execution:**\n1. User: `cloche run --workflow develop`\n2. CLI sends `RunWorkflowRequest` via gRPC\n3. Daemon launches container with `cloche-agent <workflow-file>`\n4. Agent inside container:\n   - Parses workflow DSL\n   - Launches entry step (via `prompt` or `generic` adapter)\n   - Step writes `CLOCHE_RESULT:` marker or relies on exit code\n   - Agent reads result, follows wiring, launches next step(s)\n   - Logs to unified log and status writer (JSON to stdout)\n   - Persists step outputs to `.cloche/output/*.log`\n\n**Host workflow execution:**\n1. Daemon detects host.cloche exists\n2. Runs `host.runner.RunNamed(ctx, \"list-tasks\")`\n   - Executes list-tasks workflow (script steps only)\n   - Parses output as JSONL, picks first open task\n3. Runs `host.runner.RunNamed(ctx, \"main\", taskID)`\n   - Executes script/workflow/agent steps\n   - `workflow` steps dispatch container runs via gRPC\n   - Waits for container runs to complete\n   - Can pass data via output mappings\n4. Runs `host.runner.RunNamed(ctx, \"finalize\")`\n   - Cleanup step regardless of main outcome\n\n**Data passing:**\n- Output mappings: Extract JSON from previous step → env vars\n- Output files: Read from `.cloche/<run-id>/output/`\n- Run context: Shared JSON key-value store\n- Env vars: Injected by executor into next step\n\n---\n\nThis architecture provides a flexible, extensible system for autonomous workflow execution with clear separation of concerns (DSL parsing, execution engine, adapters) and composable data-passing mechanisms suitable for AI-driven development tasks."}],"totalDurationMs":66156,"totalTokens":74062,"totalToolUseCount":30,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1247,"cache_read_input_tokens":68411,"output_tokens":4400,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1247},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
